<br>
If you're going to read this post, read the whole thing.<br>
<br>
Considering the nature of this thread, an introduction is in order on my part.  I'm a 65 necro with lot's of aa's that recently transferred to FV in order to become apart of and raid with Fire and Fury; a very well-spoken, bright and skilled group of people - contrary to what seems to be the popular label.... label?  I'm sorry, I think this thread is way beyond being sugar coated; what I meant to say is, stereotype.<br>
<br>
I see more thoughtless stereotypes being thrown around in this thread than a supremacist function in the middle of Harlem.  We all know about stereotypes, it's that matter of thinking that harvests unadulterated hate for entire factions, interests, countries and even entire races.  Now, I know, noone is burning down buildings and storming congregations with bats and shotguns; the extreme always makes points crystal clear.  So, lets get a few thing's straight and cut out the shallow stereotypes. I am posting here to defend myself and my guildmates that transferred to FV and all the new friends I have made in FnF since I transferred; chew it up or spit it out. You are free.<br>
<br>
I hate &quot;l33t ub3r d00ds&quot; that will step on anyone in order to get what they want, which is, more often than not, a less experienced and newer player, and, believe me, there are plenty of guilds out there with those type of people.  Ya know what I also hate?  Newer and less experienced individuals that hate me because of it just because I am a high end character in a high end guild.  Sounds like a vicious cycle, doesn't it?  What causes such a vicious cycle?... stereotypes.  Bob and his buddies from &lt;Uber&gt; guild go to Dawnshroud Peaks so they can grab a shard for Betty.  Meanwhile, Jack and his buddies of lower level adventureres are advancing towards the same camp that Bob and his buddies need to go to in order to grab the shard.  Confusion incurs when the two parties meet.  This type of thing happens every day on every server and time after time a lower level or newer player will feel stepped on by a higher level player because of the aforementioned stereotype... they MUST have done that on purpose; they MUST have wanted to ruin my day and take my camp.  Unfortunately, more often than not, the higher level players mean no harm and a seed of hate is planted into yet another new or lower level player.  Bare with me, the point is coming.<br>
<br>
I'll be honest with you. I dont give a fuck about newer, lower level, or casual players.  None affect me directly on a common basis; like Milow said, I rarely even have contact with lower level players save for the bazaar.  However, I do adhere to the norms of this game; low level and high level players alike - I'm even polite, and, rarely, even make friends with lower level players. Yet I see all this hate being pointed towards me, oh yes, me, by alot of people here.  There's that vicious cycle trying to start itself up.  But I didnt come here to point fingers.  I came here to convince you that these people transfering to join Fire and Fury did so in order to experience the high end game with a well organized and mature group of people.  Yes, mature.  They didn't come here to take advantage of the non-no drop clause, they didn't come here to patronize roleplayers and they certainly didnt come here to run over the high, low level population.  They, we, came here to play the game with Fire and Fury.  Just like you play the game to roleplay, make friends, or just kill time; and none are less important than any other.  As far as people transfering to FV for other reasons, whether it be to roleplay, join a different guild, to take advantage of the non no-drop clause(ebay) or even simply to escape their server of origin, the only one that irks me is the taking advantage of the non no-drop clause via ebay; yeah, it's probably a plague to this server already... you cant have your cake and eat it, too.  Transfers causing a server population spike? Well, if this is your concern, I assure you it has nothing to do with FnF and it's transferees so point your finger elsewhere. FnF will recruit what they need and that's it.<br>
<br>
FnF as an entity is doing what it needs to do in order to play Everquest the way it want's to which, in this case, is recruiting across servers; and that's an admirable thing, especially for a competitive guild that plays to win.  Did you ever think of what FnF is giving up in order to re-equip and re-acquaint all these server transfer people like me?  It's an admirable thing, indeed.  If you feel you are being stepped on because FnF is recruiting cross servers or because these &quot;people&quot; are moving to your server to join FnF, you should consider re-thinking things.  If you don't, thanks in advance; we're happy to be here.<br>
<br>
